<subSubSection pageId="27" pageNumber="28" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="27.[151,1436,353,847]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,750,776]" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">Remarks.</emphasis>
This species resembles 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Gong, Zhu &amp; Chen" authorityYear="2018" box="[585,767,749,776]" class="Insecta" family="Drosophilidae" genus="Phortica" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="27" pageNumber="28" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="semiannulata">
<emphasis box="[585,602,750,775]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">P</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[616,767,749,775]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="28">semiannulata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in having the anterior, more or less inward oriented postgonites articulated to tips of sclerotized arch on the anterior margin of aedeagal sheath, but can be distinguished from it by the diagnostic characters.
</paragraph>
